Russian Equity Movers: Concern Kalina, Polymetal, Protek

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-04-15T15:33:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/russian-equity-movers-concern-kalina-polymetal-protek.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.1
percent to 1,780.36 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index gained 0.1 percent to 2,030.32.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Concern  Kalina (KLNA)  , a Russian cosmetics maker,
advanced to its highest since November 2007, adding 2.4 percent
to 1,054.9 rubles after its board recommended a dividend of
38.83 rubles for the second half of last year and the company
bought out ordinary shares amounting to 2.47 billion rubles ($87
million).  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian producer of gold and
silver, snapped four days of losses, adding 5.4 percent to 599.5
rubles as gold gained to a record and silver climbed the highest
in 31 years.  OAO  Protek (PRTK)   retreated to its lowest in more than a
week, slipping 3.5 percent to 41.06 rubles after the Federal
Anti-Monopoly Service said it was investigating charges the
Russian drugs wholesaler colluded on government drug supply
tenders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
